<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Possibly Classic Shell related Outlook 2010, Chrome prob]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=2022&amp;p=10172#p10172"><![CDATA[
For your Outlook and Excel problems, try uninstalling Classic Shell and see if the problems persist. Classic Shell should not affect the behavior of any Office products.<br /><br />As for Chrome, I think there is a bug in how they handle icons. Every time you run Chrome it rebuilds its jumplist (the links you see in the menu). It deletes the old icons and creates new ones. Unfortunately that also deletes the icons for the pinned links. You will get a similar problem if you pin Chrome to the taskbar and not even use the start menu.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=2">Ivo</a> — Sat Jan 18, 2014 4:52 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
